This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with part segmentation of objects in images. It also involves deep learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a self-supervised approach, which involves learning from unlabeled data, making it relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves semantic consistency across different object instances, which makes it relevant to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on different types of image collections, which makes it relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
